HEADWORD: Kilowatt hour
<hw>Kil"o*watt` hour</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A unit of work or
energy equal to that done by one kilowatt acting for one hour; --
approximately equal to 1.34 horse-power hour.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

